The paper discusses the foundational standards of the Web of Data, which include the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) and the Resource Description Framework (RDF). These standards are commonly used in the field of databases (cs.DB) for representing and interrelating data. The paper also discusses the use of RDF for knowledge representation and reasoning, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the advantages of separating RDF from its logic language legacy, which is relevant to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
